sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Training Operator Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS (self-signed)
    participant Operator as Training Operator Controller<br/>8080/TCP metrics, 8081/TCP health
    participant DNS as Kubernetes DNS<br/>53/UDP
    participant Master as Master Pod<br/>23456/TCP (PyTorch)
    participant Workers as Worker Pods<br/>Framework-specific ports

    Note over User, Workers: Flow 1: PyTorch Distributed Training Job Lifecycle

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply PyTorchJob CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (kubeconfig)
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-kubeflow-org-v1-pytorchjob<br/>TLS (self-signed), API server client cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Admission Response (Allow/Deny)
    K8sAPI-->>User: CR created

    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch event: PyTorchJob created<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Master Pod + Headless Service<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Worker Pods + Headless Services + Init Containers<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicy (PyTorch only)<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token

    Note over DNS, Workers: Init containers wait for master DNS resolution

    Workers->>DNS: Resolve master pod FQDN<br/>53/UDP, No encryption
    DNS-->>Workers: Master pod IP

    Workers->>Master: NCCL/Gloo distributed training<br/>23456/TCP, No encryption

    Note over Operator, K8sAPI: Operator monitors pod status and updates job conditions

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Update PyTorchJob/status<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Cleanup pods/services on completion<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token

    Note over User, Workers: Flow 2: MPI Job with Launcher/Worker (kubectl-exec pattern)

    participant Launcher as Launcher Pod<br/>kubectl exec
    participant MPIWorkers as MPI Worker Pods<br/>sleep 365d

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply MPIJob CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI-->>User: CR created

    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch event: MPIJob created

    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create ConfigMap (hostfile, kubexec.sh)<br/>HTTPS/443
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create SA, Role, RoleBinding for launcher<br/>HTTPS/443
    Note right of Operator: Role scoped to worker pod names only
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Worker Pods (sleep 365d)<br/>HTTPS/443
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Launcher Pod (kubectl-delivery init)<br/>HTTPS/443

    Launcher->>K8sAPI: pods/exec to worker pods<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token (RBAC-scoped)
    K8sAPI->>MPIWorkers: Execute MPI commands via kubectl exec
    MPIWorkers-->>K8sAPI: Command output
    K8sAPI-->>Launcher: Exec result
